   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zimbabwe Cash Preparedness</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Start and End dates: 23rd April 2019 &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x201C; 31st August 2021
Summary:&#xC2;&#xA0; Resilience through Disaster Response Management; Multipurpose Cash Preparedness and Comprehensive School SafetyWorking with the Finnish Red Cross, and WFP - Based in Harare and Mangwe district
1.&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0; Strengthened capacities to use multi-purpose cash transfer as a mean of humanitarian aid delivery mechanism
2.&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0; Children and youth, and their home communities, are more resilient to disasters and have safer learning environments through the enhanced contribution of the Red Cross to the Comprehensive School Safety Framework in Zimbabwe.
3.&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0; Distribution of first aid, basic safety and student care equipment to schools as well as distribution of IEC materials for youth and children.
&#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0;ECHO 2018 - Activities were extended to Dec 2020 - in a non cost extension due to COVID. BRC completed all CASH related activities.&#xC2;&#xA0;
&#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0;ECHO 2020 - Implementation started in Sept 2020 and will continue for 1 year, BRC will continue holding the lead for CASH Prep. Co-funding was covered by CASH team with over 80K to cover CASH and Social Protection.&#xC2;&#xA0;
&#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0; &#xC2;&#xA0;ECHO 2021&#xC2;&#xA0; - BRC will not be entering into this consortium.&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;
E
Location: Zimbabwe &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x201C; Harare and Mangwe district
Bens: Direct beneficiaries of the entire programme - 23,060 people
Donor: ECHO and General funds 
PNSs: Finnish Red Cross 
&#xC2;</narrative>
  </description>
